## CIBA in MCP Server

The MCP server can initiate CIBA to step up permissions for a tool call:

```typescript
// CIBAPendingRequest (stored in BankingSession)
interface CIBAPendingRequest {
  authReqId: string;
  initiatedAt: number;   // epoch ms
  expiresAt: number;     // epoch ms
  interval: number;      // poll interval seconds
  userEmail: string;
  requiredScope: string;
}

// When step-up auth is needed:
// 1. MCP server calls banking_api_server POST /api/auth/ciba/initiate
// 2. Returns auth_req_id to session, sends notification to UI
// 3. MCP server polls banking_api_server GET /api/auth/ciba/poll/:authReqId
// 4. On approval, tokens added to session, tool execution continues
```

