## BankingAPIClient — Calling the API Server

```typescript
// Use this.apiClient in tool handlers — never use fetch directly
import { BankingAPIClient } from '../banking/BankingAPIClient';

// GET with session token
const accounts = await this.apiClient.get('/api/accounts', session);

// POST with body
const result = await this.apiClient.post('/api/transactions/transfer', {
  fromAccountId,
  toAccountId,
  amount,
}, session);

// apiClient picks the right token from session.userTokens automatically
// Throws BankingAPIError on non-2xx responses
// Throws AuthenticationError (with AuthErrorCodes) on 401/403
```

---

## Server Capabilities Declaration

Declared in `MCPMessageHandler`:

```typescript
private readonly serverCapabilities: ServerCapabilities = {
  tools: { listChanged: false },
  logging: {},
  prompts: { listChanged: false },
  resources: { subscribe: false, listChanged: false },
};
```

Do not change `listChanged` to `true` without implementing the `tools/listChanged` notification.

