## Deployment

The MCP server is **not** deployed to Vercel. It needs an always-on WebSocket host:

| Platform | Free tier | Deploy command |
|----------|-----------|----------------|
| Railway | ~$5/mo | `railway up` |
| Render | Free (sleeps after 15min) | Connect GitHub repo |
| Fly.io | Free (3 shared VMs) | `fly deploy` |

```bash
# Build
cd banking_mcp_server
npm run build:clean   # rm -rf dist && tsc

# Run in production
npm run start:prod    # NODE_ENV=production node dist/index.js

# Env vars required on MCP server host:
BANKING_API_URL=https://banking-demo-puce.vercel.app
PINGONE_AUTH_URL=https://auth.pingone.com/{envId}/as
ADMIN_CLIENT_ID=...
ADMIN_CLIENT_SECRET=...
PORT=8080
```

After deploying, set `MCP_SERVER_URL=wss://your-mcp-host` in the Vercel project settings.
